The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 September is 3,403 (393.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 117 new confirmed cases (13.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 September, there were 110 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 6% (7 extra cases).
